!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

soak /səʊk/

(soaking,soaked,soaks) 

1. V-T/V-I If you soak something or leave it to soak , you put it into a liquid and leave it there. 浸泡 

例： Soak the beans for 2 hours. 把豆子泡上两个小时。 

2. V-T If a liquid soaks something or if you soak something with a liquid, the liquid makes the thing very wet. 使浸湿 

例： The water had soaked his jacket and shirt. 水浸湿了他的夹克和衬衣。 

3. V-I If a liquid soaks through something, it passes through it. 渗透 

例： There was so much blood it had soaked through my boxer shorts. 血出得太多，都渗透了我的平脚短裤。 

4. V-I If someone soaks , they spend a long time in a hot bath, because they enjoy it. 长时间泡浴 

例： What I need is to soak in a hot tub. 我需要的是在浴盆里泡个热水澡。 

5. N-COUNT Soak is also a noun. 泡浴 

例： I was having a long soak in the bath. 我当时正在浴室里长时间地泡浴。 

6.  →  see also soaked , soaking

</div>

